CNCP v1 22994
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#6499: Allow omit space around `of` in `v-for`",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:25:43.753716+00:00",
  "text": "Allow omit space around `of` in `v-for`\n\n### What problem does this feature solve?\r\n\r\n`v-for` is similar to `for..of`/`for..in` loop in JavaScript.\r\n\r\nIn JavaScript, the following is valid\r\n\r\n```js\r\nfor (const{x}of[{x:1}])\r\n\tconsole.log(x)\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut in Vue SFC, the following is NOT valid\r\n\r\n```vue\r\n<div v-for=\"{x} of[{x:'1'}]\">{{ x }}</div>\r\n```\r\n\r\nthe space around `of` can't be omitted. [playground](https://sfc.vuejs.org/#eNp9js8KwjAMh1+l5OLFtXgdU/A5jIfpMt2wf0i7OSh9d1sREQVvyS9fviTC3jk5TwQ1oGkCaXdrA+3QCNF0wyzmqre8RYhLErY/xKVebVbpiLCLUSwipUZlLPONei/DGgbtLIdKt06O3ppsj0WJr4FHqMUzKVk+X3qEawjO10r5/lx+Gr20fFG5kjyZMGiS5HV1Ynv3xFmMsP5wqBzOxBWT6YiJ/zm/0B9v0SY0CdID86RkEg==)\r\n\r\nSince in JavaScript it's fine to not add spaces around `of`, sometimes I don't write it, let Prettier to add space for me. Then I wrote the same in Vue SFC, it can't work.\r\n\r\nCan we support it?\r\n\r\n### What does the proposed API look like?\r\n\r\nN/A",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request",
    "scope: compiler",
    ":cake: p2-nice-to-have"
  ],
